PDCP SDU delay

panels.description:
This KPI shows the average estimated F1 round trip delay between CU and MAC DU, measured on gNB and per DU. It is the time:
- Starting when the PDCP PDU packet is sent by CU over F1 (PDCP PDU packet has left CU)
Then, this PDCP PDU packet is going until MAC PDU (of DU). When the 1st segment is ready to be sent on the air for the first time (excluding repetitions), the MAC PDU sends a DDDS to CU.
- And ending when the DDDS (sent by the MAC PDU) message is received by CU over F1 to acknowledge the packet (removed from CU buffer).
Note:
- We can consider that the time to process the DDDS message is equivalent to a PDU message received on CU over F1 and the PDU was sent by MAC PDU.
